  "texts": [
    "Specifically, these models use distinct GNNs to aggregate spatial information on each graph snapshot individually.",
    "The outputs from the different time steps are then fed into a temporal module for sequence modeling.",
    "Therefore, given a graph at time, the representation is computed as follows:Z t = f ( G t), H t = g ( H t-1, Z t), (3) f G t Z t g H t-1 Z t H t f gwhere is a GNN model used to encode and obtain the graph representation at this time step.",
    "is a sequence model such as RNN, used to integrate the previous hidden state and current graph representation to update the current hidden state.",
    "Manessi et al. [36] use this architecture to propose CD-GCN and WD-GCN models, where is a GCN model and uses a standard Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM)."
